article.headline: Arizona State 68, Washington State 61
article.story:
TEMPE, Ariz. (AP) -- Kylan Loney scored a career-high 24 points,
including five 3-pointers, to lead Arizona State past Washington
State 68-61 Saturday night in the Pacific 10 Conference opener for
both teams.

Carrie Buckner added 15 points for the Sun Devils (7-3), which
have won five of their last six. Bianca McCall had 20 points for
the Cougars (4-6), who lost their fourth in a row.

Arizona State took advantage of 29 Washington State turnovers,
scoring 28 points off those miscues.

Stephanie Singer added 12 points for the Cougars, who have lost
24 consecutive Pac-10 road games dating back to 2001.

The Sun Devils overcame a 34 percent shooting night (21 of 62),
making 9 of 22 from beyond the 3-point line.

Washington State led 35-30 at the half and 43-28 with 12:32
remaining, but Arizona State went on a 14-5 run over the next six
minutes and led the rest of the way.
